"Dear Mr. Wilkerson,

As much as I sympathize with your complaint, I must decline your request to relocate the Code Puncher. In order to transport it down the elevator I would have to disassemble the apparatus, which is something I cannot take responsibility for, as the puncher contains a considerable amount of very fragile machinery. 
Consequently, to acquire a new Punch Card for the Maintenance Units, the procedure remains the same: Send somebody to my tower to convey the Service Point Number and I shall provide the messenger with the card right away.

Yours sincerely,
George Boleston"